Another interesting point which may be mentioned is that of the emission of high-speed electrons from the white dwarfs, which are almost completely degenerate, and hence the chances of collision for an escaping electron are very small. These high-speed electrons will in some cases have energies comparable to the cosmic radiation. In fact, it can be easily seen that due to this electron escape a black dwarf will lose almost all of its mass-the final state of a black dwarf is a diffuse mass. These considerations will be published elsewhere in detail.
